content:
Add an Icon to a FlexCard

Display an SVG Icon on a FlexCard. Select from a Salesforce SVG icon or a custom action. You can also link the icon to an action.

From the FlexCard Designer, drag an Icon element from the Build panel into a state on the canvas.
(Optional) Update the element name in the Element Name field.
Select an icon type.
Configure a Custom icon by entering its source in the Source field or select an icon from the Icon field.
To link the icon to an action, click + Add Action. Configure action properties.

Icon element properties are configurable in the Property Panel when you select an Icon element in the FlexCard Designer. Display a Salesforce SVG Icon or a custom icon on a FlexCard. 

Style your icon element by clicking Style to open the Style panel.

Preview your FlexCard. See Preview a FlexCard.
title: FlexCards: Adding Icons to a FlexCard
